UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1069
1 AN ACT relating to coverage for scalp cooling systems used in connection with
2 chemotherapy treatment for breast cancer.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 17A OF KRS CHAPTER 304
5 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) "Health plan":
8 1. Means any health insurance policy, certificate, contract, or plan that
9 offers or provides coverage in this state for chemotherapy treatment
10 for breast cancer:
11 a. By direct payment, reimbursement, or otherwise; and
12 b. On a fully insured or self-insured basis or any combination
13 thereof; and
14 2. Includes a health benefit plan; and
15 (b) "Scalp cooling system" means any device used to cool the scalp to prevent
16 or reduce hair loss during chemotherapy treatment.
17 (2) To the extent permitted by federal law, a health plan shall provide coverage for
18 scalp cooling systems used in connection with chemotherapy treatment for breast
19 cancer.
20 (3) If the application of any requirement of this section to a qualified health plan, as
21 defined in 42 U.S.C. sec. 18021(a)(1), as amended, results or would result in a
22 determination that the state must make payments to defray the cost of the
23 requirement under 42 U.S.C. sec. 18031(d)(3) and 45 C.F.R. sec. 155.170, as
24 amended, then the requirement shall not apply to the qualified health plan until
25 the requirement to make cost defrayal payments is no longer applicable.
26 Section 2. KRS 304.17A-099 is amended to read as follows:
27 (1) As used in this section, "qualified health plan" has the same meaning as in 42
