3 (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, if the application of a
4 provision of this chapter results, or would result, in a determination that the
5 state must make payments to defray the cost of the provision under 42 U.S.C.
6 sec. 18031(d)(3) and 45 C.F.R. sec. 155.170, as amended, then the provision
7 shall not apply to a qualified health plan or any other health insurance policy,
8 certificate, plan, or contract until the requirement to make cost defrayal
9 payments is no longer applicable; and
10 (b) This subsection shall not apply to any of the following:
11 1. A provision of this chapter that became effective on or before January 1,
12 2024; or
13 2. Section 1 of this Act.
14 (3) To the extent permitted by federal law, if the state is required under 42 U.S.C. sec.
15 18031(d)(3) and 45 C.F.R. sec. 155.170, as amended, to make payments to defray
16 the cost of a provision of this chapter:
17 (a) 1. Each qualified health plan issuer shall determine, and provide to the
18 commissioner, the cost attributable to the provision for the qualified
19 health plan.
20 2. The cost attributable to a provision for a qualified health plan under
21 subparagraph 1. of this paragraph shall be:
22 a. Calculated in accordance with generally accepted actuarial
23 principles and methodologies;
24 b. Conducted by a member of the American Academy of Actuaries;
25 and
26 c. Reported by the qualified health plan issuer to:
27 i. The commissioner; and
