1 ii. The Division of Health Benefit Exchange within the Office
2 of Data Analytics;
3 (b) The commissioner shall use the information obtained under paragraph (a) of
4 this subsection to determine the statewide average of the cost attributable to
5 the provision for all qualified health plan issuers to which the provision is
6 applicable; and
7 (c) The required payments shall be:
8 1. Calculated based on the statewide average of the cost attributable to the
9 provision as determined by the commissioner under paragraph (b) of this
10 subsection; and
11 2. Submitted directly to qualified health plan issuers by the department
12 through a process established by the commissioner.
13 (4) A qualified health plan issuer that receives a payment under subsection (3)(c)2. of
14 this section shall:
15 (a) Reduce the premium charged to an individual on whose behalf the issuer
16 received the payment in an amount equal to the amount of the payment; or
17 (b) Notwithstanding KRS 304.12-090, provide a premium rebate to an individual
18 on whose behalf the issuer received the payment in an amount equal to the
19 amount of the payment.
20 (5) Any fines collected for violations of this section shall be:
21 (a) Placed in a trust and agency account within the department, which shall not
22 lapse; and
23 (b) Used solely by the department to make payments in accordance with
24 subsection (3)(c)2. of this section.
25 (6) The commissioner shall promulgate any administrative regulations necessary to
26 enforce and effectuate this section.
